<div class="container-narrow">
    <h1>Community Guidelines</h1>

    <div class="restaurant-detail">
        <h2>Our Mission</h2>
        <p>DLSU Eats is a platform for the DLSU community to discover, review, and share their dining experiences. We're committed to maintaining a respectful, honest, and helpful environment for all users.</p>

        <hr>

        <h2>Review Guidelines</h2>
        <h3>Be Honest and Fair</h3>
        <p>Share your genuine experience. Reviews should reflect your actual visit to the restaurant. Don't exaggerate or misrepresent your experience.</p>
        <h3>Be Respectful</h3>
        <p>Express your opinions constructively. Avoid offensive language, personal attacks, or discriminatory remarks. Critique the food and service, not the people.</p>
        <h3>Be Detailed</h3>
        <p>Help others make informed decisions. Mention specific dishes, describe the atmosphere, comment on service quality, and explain your rating.</p>
        <h3>Be Relevant</h3>
        <p>Keep your review focused on your dining experience. Reviews about unrelated topics may be removed.</p>

        <hr>

        <h2>What's Not Allowed</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Fake Reviews:</strong> Don't review restaurants you haven't visited or post reviews on behalf of others</li>
            <li><strong>Conflicts of Interest:</strong> Disclose if you have a relationship with the restaurant (employee, owner, competitor)</li>
            <li><strong>Harassment:</strong> Don't attack other reviewers or restaurant staff personally</li>
            <li><strong>Spam:</strong> Don't post promotional content, advertisements, or irrelevant links</li>
            <li><strong>Offensive Content:</strong> No hate speech, profanity, or inappropriate content</li>
            <li><strong>Private Information:</strong> Don't share others' personal information without consent</li>
        </ul>

        <hr>

        <h2>For Restaurant Owners</h2>
        <h3>Responding to Reviews</h3>
        <p>We encourage owners to respond to reviews professionally and constructively. Thank customers for positive feedback and address concerns raised in negative reviews.</p>
        <h3>Don't:</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Post fake positive reviews or ask others to do so</li>
            <li>Attack or threaten reviewers</li>
            <li>Offer incentives for positive reviews or to remove negative ones</li>
        </ul>

        <hr>

        <h2>Helpful vs. Unhelpful</h2>
        <p>Use the helpful/unhelpful buttons to highlight quality reviews. Helpful reviews are detailed, balanced, and provide useful information to other diners.</p>

        <hr>

        <h2>Reporting Violations</h2>
        <p>If you see content that violates these guidelines, please report it. We review all reports and take appropriate action.</p>

        <hr>

        <h2>Consequences</h2>
        <p>Violations of these guidelines may result in:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Review removal</li>
            <li>Account warnings</li>
            <li>Temporary or permanent account suspension</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-muted mt-2">Last updated: 2026</p>
    </div>

    <div class="text-center mt-2">
        <a href="/" class="btn btn-primary">Back to Home</a>
    </div>
</div>
